Message 3 Subject: Re: Potential Guest for Sales POP! Podcasts: Latoya Brooks
Message 3 Content: Hi Latoya, Thank you for reaching out and showing interest in being interviewed on SalesPOP! A warm welcome to you on SalesPOP! SalesPOP! is a platform to educate, inspire, motivate, and connect. To be in our circle means that you will meet like-minded people, learn from them, get inspired, connect, and create a win-win. We are handpicking every one of them by looking thoroughly at their work, messages, books, speeches, and projects. SalesPOP! was founded a couple of years ago as the extended arm of pipelinersales ( www.pipelinersales.com ), a company founded by Nikolaus Kimla ( https://www.linkedin.com/in/nikolauskimla/ ). He is a true entrepreneur and leader for more than 25 years and stands for the mission and philosophy of our daily business. Pipelinersales stands out not only through its amazing product but also because of the philosophy behind it - the Austrian School of Economics. We firmly believe that only ongoing education can guarantee sustainable success within and through the work of a company. Education can happen in many ways, but we must always be equipped with the right toolset to master whatever challenge comes our way. This toolset needs to be updated occasionally and brought to state-of-the-art. The daily challenges require us to stay flexible and be prepared for the unprecedented by updating our “toolbox” constantly. The interview takes about 15-20 minutes and is conducted by our CMO and editor-in-chief, John Golden ( https://www.linkedin.com/in/johngolden/ ). Please find John Golden’s Calendly link below: https://scheduler.pipelinersales.com/john-golden/sales-pop-interview After the interview is recorded, it will be turned into a podcast so that our international audience can listen to it anytime and wherever they are. We will also set up your contributor page, where everything about you and your work and publications will be featured. Please send us updates about events, book releases, etc..! The interviews and podcasts are published on our website, our YouTube channel, and various podcast channels. They are promoted and shared through our various social media channels, our YouTube channel, weekly emails and newsletters, and by the interviewees. Last but not least, would you please provide me with a short bio, a headshot and all your social media links including your LinkedIn profile?! We are excited to welcome you for an interview. If you have any questions, please don't hesitate to reach out anytime! Kind regards, Claudia Claudia Kimla-Stern VP Talent Relations SalesPOP! Message 2 Subject: Re: Potential Guest for Think Business with Tyler: Latoya Brooks
Message 2 Content: Hi Latoya - We appreciate you reaching out and for thinking of the podcast.. After reviewing the suggestion, I don’t think it's the right fit for the show. The podcast focuses on real-world entrepreneurial journeys from business owners who have built and scaled 7- and 8-figure companies . We aim to share insights from entrepreneurs who have navigated the challenges of growth, hiring, leadership, and scaling a business - not just from a strategic level, but from lived experience. At this time, we are not featuring: 🚫 Marketing agencies 🚫 Business coaches or consultants (unless they have scaled a business previously) 🚫 Real estate professionals 🚫 Financial advisors or wealth managers 🚫 Law or tax firms We are specifically looking for business owners and entrepreneurs who have built their businesses beyond $1M+ in annual revenue and can share actionable lessons from their journey - whether that’s scaling pains, hiring challenges, operational insights, or leadership struggles. If you know someone who fits this profile, we’d love to hear about them. Otherwise, We sincerely appreciate you reaching out, and wish you all the best! Best, The Podcast Team

Message 1 Subject: Potential Guest for Technology Revolution: The Future of Now: Latoya Brooks
Message 1 Content: Dear Technology Revolution: The Future of Now Team,
Message 2 Subject: Re: Potential Guest for Technology Revolution: The Future of Now: Latoya Brooks
Message 2 Content: Hello, Latoya: Thank you for your interest in my show. However, it is clear that you have not watched or listened to Technology Revolution: The Future of Now and you are not familiar with my format or topics. The show is NOT a 1:1 interview, not a Q&A, not a webinar, NEVER advice for the audience, not a marketing venue or political platform. My format is a 4-Futurist round table sharing their sound-bite predictions on my topic of the week – “The Future of ___ + AI”…. [an industry / business / creative genre / skill set / lifestyle … ] I welcome topic suggestions and if I agree to the topic, the person making the pitch then engages a full panel of four Futurists from different organizations. I receive pitches like yours several times a week – usually from PR agencies – and I am amazed [and sad] that they know nothing about my show.

Message 2 Content: Hi Latoya, Thanks so much for reaching out! I’m always looking for high-quality guests, and I appreciate your interest in being on the Happier at Work® podcast. The podcast is aimed at client-facing leaders in global organisations, covering topics like workplace culture, leadership, employee engagement, and career development. If your expertise aligns with these areas, I’d love for you to take the next steps below. How to Apply as a Guest: ✅ Listen to the podcast – We prioritize guests who are familiar with the show. If you haven’t already, you can check it out here: Happier at Work Podcast ✅ Guest scheduling & backlog – We’re currently reviewing guests for end of 2025, and there is a six-month backlog. We’ll be in touch if we think it’s a great fit. ✅ Submit your interest – You’re welcome to express interest here , and we’ll review your application in due course. Looking to Improve Your Podcast Guesting Strategy? I also run an award-winning programme, Podcast Guesting Mastery , which helps experts and business leaders like you get booked on the right podcasts, craft compelling pitches, deliver standout interviews, and maximize visibility afterward. If this sounds valuable, you can [ join the waitlist here ] to be the first to hear about the next cohort. Thanks again for reaching out—I appreciate your enthusiasm! Let me know if you have any questions.

Message 1 Content: Dear High Voltage Business Builders Podcast Team,
Message 2 Subject: Re: Potential Guest for High Voltage Business Builders Podcast: Latoya Brooks
Message 2 Content: Hi Latoya, Thank you for reaching out and for the thoughtful guest recommendation! We cover everything in E-commerce, from product development and sourcing to Amazon FBA and Facebook ads. Our episodes typically last from 30 minutes to an hour and are mostly focused on tactical advice for E-commerce sellers, but every now and then we cover broader topics such as financial independence, success, and meaning. The vast majority of our listeners are from the United States. Neil is always looking for good candidates in the areas of: Amazon FBA Shopify TikTok Shops Wholesale, Retail and Omni-Channel E-commerce Brands & Strategies Digital Marketing Strategies for E-commerce AI, User Generated Content & Anything To Create Better Brands Faster Software that supports Amazon FBA, TikTok Shops & Shopify E-commerce sellers Guests who are helping new and aspiring entrepreneurs or business owners Alternative financing, IBC, real estate, investments, and passive/active-to-passive income strategies focused on E-commerce Other things we look for in our podcast guest who want to sponsor an episode with Neil: Guests running organizations with email lists greater than 5k and large social media followings Individuals willing to collaborate on group virtual workshops and events where Neil can share the Voltage story Guests whose audiences overlap with ours—middle-aged professionals looking to build a business, retire faster than 20+ years, or create almost automated income streams through E-commerce. Please let us know if you align with these interests and qualifications. Also note that our guest episode sponsorship fee is $97 for those who would qualify for an episode. We look forward to potentially featuring you on our platform!
Message 3 Subject: Re: Potential Guest for High Voltage Business Builders Podcast: Latoya Brooks
Message 3 Content: Hi Nicole, I’m so grateful for your interest in having me on your show. Given my excitement about appearing on more podcasts, I sent a number of inquiries to hosts in the last week and was actually astonished by the strong response I received.  In light of how many invitations I’ve received, my calendar is now overflowing, and I’ve realized I can no longer add more interview bookings for the foreseeable future.  I really appreciate your response and apologize for reaching out to request an opportunity and now being unable to accept it.
Message 4 Subject: Re: Potential Guest for High Voltage Business Builders Podcast: Latoya Brooks
Message 4 Content: Hi Latoya, Thank you for your thoughtful message! I completely understand how quickly schedules can fill up, and I truly appreciate you keeping me updated. I’m glad to hear you’ve received such an overwhelming response—that’s fantastic! No need to apologize at all. If things open up in the future and you’d like to revisit the opportunity, we’d love to have you. Wishing you continued success with your interviews and all that you’re working on! Best, Nicole McClain Executive Assistant Voltage Holdings, LLC -- To your success, Neil Twa CEO, Voltage Holdings, LLC Amazon Management & Growth Consultants A by-invitation-only community of CEOs and entrepreneurs https://voltagedm.com Text/SMS: +1 (417)

Message 2 Subject: Re: Potential Guest for The Modern Manager: Latoya Brooks
Message 2 Content: Hi Latoya, I know you didn't ask for any advice, so I hope you'll forgive me for being so forward. As a podcast host, it's important to me to only accept qualified individuals to be guests, which means I have to carefully vet each request. Your areas of expertise sound great, but there is nothing on your website or that you provided to me that would allow me to understand why you are qualified to speak about those topics (no articles you've written, prior guest appearances, etc) so I'm not able to adequately assess you as a guest. I know that it can be hard early on when trying to get your first guest appearance, which may not be your case and if so, I hope you'll send me examples from your prior work, but even if you record a few solo videos and put them on your website, where you can showcase your ability to present your thoughts on a given topic, it would go far in positioning you as a qualified expert. Again, apologies if I've overstepped here. I don't write personal notes to many people, but I try to be supportive of young women in this space because I remember how hard it was for me to get my footing. Wishing you all the best, Mamie

Message 3 Subject: RE: Potential Guest for Software People Stories: Latoya Brooks
Message 3 Content: Latoya, Thanks for reaching out and offering to share your story on the podcast. I looked at the suggested points for a conversation. As you may know, the Software People Stories podcast focuses more on the personal and professional journeys of our guests. It is not intended to be a technical podcast. The primary audience for the podcast are people associated with software. If your experience in helping teams and individuals also covers the IT industry, along with your own experience as a business strategist, it would make it interesting and valuable for the listeners. These are unscripted conversations, that start with a self-introduction and then I let my curiosity take over. If you are comfortable with this format and focus, we can work out a mutually convenient time to record. I record the conversation on Zoom. I am based in Bangalore, India [IST is 5:30 hours ahead of UTC]. Where are you based? Regards Shiv Please share your thoughts on My work blogs and my Podcast S Sivaguru 354/3, 1st Cross, 1st Block, Jayanagar, Bangalore - 560 011

Message 1 Subject: Potential Guest for The Prison Officer Podcast: Latoya Brooks
Message 1 Content: Dear The Prison Officer Podcast Team,
Message 2 Subject: RE: Potential Guest for The Prison Officer Podcast: Latoya Brooks
Message 2 Content: Dear Latoya, Thank you for reaching out and expressing interest in appearing on The Prison Officer Podcast. I genuinely appreciate you thinking of us. I wanted to take a moment to clarify the focus of our show. The Prison Officer Podcast maintains a very specific mission: to spotlight the experiences of those who have served as correctional officers - the men and women who know firsthand what it means to sit 16 hours in a Segregation Unit, eat meals off inmate trays, and handle the most challenging aspects of institutional life, including responding to violence, and inmate self-harm incidents. Our podcast was created specifically to give voice to these "forgotten cops" of our jails and prisons who often receive the leftover equipment, leftover training, and leftover respect within the criminal justice system. I've made a commitment to put their stories and experiences at the forefront. Based on your background, I don't believe our podcast would be the right platform for your expertise at this time. However, I'm always open to discussing this further if you feel there's an angle I've overlooked regarding your connection to correctional work. If you'd like to discuss this further, feel free to reach me directly at mike

After careful consideration, however, we've decided to pursue a different direction for upcoming episodes, and unfortunately, we won't be able to accommodate additional guests at this time. Please know that this decision wasn't easy, as we truly value the insights and expertise you could bring to our platform. We're continuously exploring various themes and subjects for future episodes, and I'll keep your contact information on file for potential opportunities that align more closely with our focus. Thank you once again for your interest and understanding. We wish you all the best in your endeavors, and hope our paths cross again in the future! Gratefully, Taylor (she/her) Operations Manager | Psychedelic Passage PsychedelicPassage.com Subscribe to Our Podcast Psychedelic Passage is a referral service and any referrals to third-party Service Providers in our network are informational, for your convenience only, and based on the criteria you provide to us. Message 1 Subject: Potential Guest for Language of the Soul Podcast: Latoya Brooks
Message 1 Content: Dear Language of the Soul Podcast Team,
Message 2 Subject: Re: Potential Guest for Language of the Soul Podcast: Latoya Brooks
Message 2 Content: Hello Latoya, We're thrilled to have you on board for the Language of the Soul Podcast. Your willingness to share your insights and stories with us—and, by extension, our listeners—promises to make for an enriching episode that aligns perfectly with our mission to delve deep into the cultural impact of storytelling. As partners in this journey, Dominick Domingo and I are eager to weave your unique perspectives into the fabric of our podcast. Since launching in November 2023, we've amassed over 50 insightful episodes, engaging audiences on all major podcast platforms, including Apple Podcasts, Spotify, Amazon Music, YouTube, IHeartRadio, and Buzzsprout, to name a few. Your voice is set to join a diverse chorus of storytellers who have captivated our listeners with their compelling narratives. For that reason, to let you know a bit about the spirit and intent of the podcast, here’s a brief description: LANGUAGE of the SOUL Podcast Based on Dominick Domingo’s acclaimed book by the same name, Language of the Soul Podcast explores the infinite ways in which life, simply put, is story. Individually, we’re all products of the stories we’ve been exposed to. Collectively, culture is the sum of its history. Our respective worldviews are little more than stories we tell about ourselves. Socialization is the amalgamation of narratives we weave about the human condition, shaping everything from the codes we live by to policy itself. Language of the Soul Podcast spotlights master storytellers in the Arts and Entertainment, from cinema to the literary realm. It explores topical social issues through the lens of narrative, with an eye on the march toward human potential. And as always, a nudge to embrace the power of story in our lives… Here's What Happens Next? Scheduling Your Episode: We're excited to find a time that fits your schedule for our conversation. Please choose a recording slot via our scheduling link: https://calendar.google.com/calendar/u/0/appointments/schedules/AcZssZ0_49qZE7cccMlxTT43LvGMx1FrapXTccZ54VIrRUETUmweQ-fM1aGofYva0fAkaDJlM-57pPG0?gv=true . Our recording sessions are conducted on Sundays between 11 AM and 6 PM PST, utilizing Zoom for an audio-only format to ensure comfort and flexibility. Getting to Know You Better: Understanding your journey and the stories you wish to share is crucial for a meaningful conversation. We kindly ask you to complete our brief guest questionnaire here: https://docs.google.com/forms/d/e/1FAIpQLScj_A2ZT4uSRt37IAqRt0sTjiAo0fYKGd7z_I7hqqKpfc99IQ/viewform?usp=sf_link . This form is an opportunity to share your preferred bio, any links you'd like featured alongside your episode, and the topics or stories you're passionate about. Completing this form lets Dominick fully understand who you are as our guest. *Please note that if this form is not completed, we will need to cancel you as a guest. We do this because we want to put out good content and have you represented in the best light possible, and only you can do that by answering our questions as completely as possible . Preparing for the Recording: Before our recording session, we'll email you the final details, including the Zoom link, and address any queries you might have. This pre-session communication is the perfect opportunity to highlight specific themes or questions you'd like us to cover. Looking Ahead: Your contribution to the Language of the Soul Podcast is invaluable. It's not merely about sharing your narrative; it's about igniting inspiration and offering enlightenment through the compelling power of stories. We are dedicated to crafting an episode that not only showcases your unique contributions but also deeply resonates with our audience. We highly suggest listening to a few of our episodes before scheduling your appearance on our show. We eagerly anticipate you joining us to share your story with the world. In the meantime, please don't hesitate to contact us if you have any questions or require additional information.

Message 1 Content: Dear Business of Tech: Daily 10-Minute IT Services Insights Team,
Message 2 Subject: Re: Potential Guest for Business of Tech: Daily 10-Minute IT Services Insights: Latoya Brooks
Message 2 Content: Latoya: Thanks for reaching out. I’m really looking for stories, not people.   I have a whole page and video about what I’m looking for, and it’s available here: https://www.businessof.tech/press-briefings-and-podcast-bookings/ Please know… I get a lot of pitches that can be boiled down to “This person is really smart.”.    I’m generally assuming both intelligence in the guests and in my audience — so everyone is smart. Also know that “Predictions and Trends”, “Insights into AI”, “All about Customer Experience”, “How to be a Thought Leader”, or “How to drive more sales” are not stories I’m looking for, and I’m not focused on the enterprenuerial journey as a story. You’re welcome to revisit this in a way that makes sense for what I’m looking for. Dave -- Dave Sobel Host, The Business Of Tech Podcast ( Apple Podcasts , Spotify , YouTube , Website ) dave

Message 2 Subject: Re: Potential Guest for CY6 - Check Your Six: Latoya Brooks
Message 2 Content: Good afternoon Latoya, Thank you so much for reaching out, I would be honored to have you on the show. Always looking for someone that can bring a different perspective on doing business and add insight to what we are all trying to do out here as small business owners. The podcast is audio only, but I like to connect via Streamyard for the recording just so we have a visual connection, it just seems a little more personal. I will apologize ahead of time that you get to visually chat with an old dude that has a face for radio(even though we own a video production studio)🤣 The podcast is typically 30-45 minutes, sometimes longer, just depends on how well we can drive the conversation. All total it is about an hour to your time from login to completing the podcast and will focus on your background, how you got to where you are today, your business insights and then perhaps how you are giving back to the community if that is something that you do. If you are willing, I like to have just a quick Zoom call type of intro just so you can ask any question and get comfortable with how it will all happen. It is not live so there is no pressure and we are not under a time crunch so it is pretty casual, I like to have fun on the podcast and learn something along the way. Message 1 Subject: Potential Guest for The Life Shift: Latoya Brooks
Message 1 Content: Dear The Life Shift Team,
Message 2 Subject: Re: Potential Guest for The Life Shift: Latoya Brooks
Message 2 Content: Hi Latoya, Thank you for reaching out and paying attention to the show. I hope you’ve had a chance to listen to a few episodes. Secondly, I appreciate you considering being a guest on the podcast. However, to help me focus on the theme of The Life Shift, I’d like to know if you’d be willing to share a pivotal moment in your life that changed everything. These moments are usually personal and significant. I prefer to get as specific as possible. My challenge with guests is to help them identify one specific moment in their lives that changed everything. For some, it’s a phone call, an email, or a diagnosis. I like to have a conversation centered around the moment the guest feels was most pivotal. When I first started The Life Shift Podcast , I thought my life shift was when my mom passed away when I was 8. However, after recording all these conversations, I’ve reflected and narrowed down the moment. My initial shift wasn’t when she died, but when my father had to sit me down and tell me the news. The specific words he uttered, “Your mom died in an accident” (or whatever he actually said), were the moment that truly shifted my life. It’s funny how listening to others’ stories helps us reflect more deeply on our own experiences. I recorded an episode about my journey, and you might want to listen to it first: https://

Message 2 Content: Hello Latoya!  I'm always excited to meet new people...even over email! I would be honored to have you as a guest on my podcast!  I should probably double-check a couple of things just to manage expectations a bit.  My format on the podcast is somewhat "rapid fire," meaning I try to keep the entire episode to around 15 minutes.  Also, I ask the same 5 questions of all the guests.  This gives my followers different perspectives on the same concept to consider.  If that sounds okay to you, then please go to teamengagementpodcast.com where you can review the questions I'm asking the guests this season.  There's also a calendar link at the bottom of the page where you can schedule a time. Would you mind connecting with me on LinkedIn?  I always like to connect with my guests on LinkedIn when possible.  Here's my profile: https://www.linkedin.com/in/shawnjrichards/ Oh, one other thing (again, just to manage expectations): I'm currently booked through this month, so the calendar will show times in April when we can record the podcast, and then it will be released some time in May.  I hope that timing works okay for you. Thanks Latoya!  I hope to have you on the podcast soon!  Have a great day!

Message 1 Content: Dear Black Entrepreneur Experience Team,
Message 2 Subject: Re: Potential Guest for Black Entrepreneur Experience: Latoya Brooks
Message 2 Content: Hello Latoya, Thank you for ensuring all correspondence with Dr. Richards addresses her as "Dr." to properly reflect her professional title and qualifications. Please also remind clients to do the same. Failure to adhere to this moving forward will result in future correspondence being marked as spam. We appreciate your interest and are excited to have you appear on Black Entrepreneur Experience podcast as an innovative thinker! To ensure the highest quality of content and cover our production costs, we have a nominal appearance fee of $150 per guest. Once the fee is paid and the guest release form is signed and returned, we will provide you with a link to schedule the episode. Please note that this fee is non-refundable in the case of a no-show or cancellation. Fun Facts About Beepodast Audience: Our audience is made up of diverse entrepreneurs, from startups and aspiring business owners to seasoned veterans, as well as people who actively support the entrepreneurial ecosystem. We have roughly 60% men and 40% women listeners. Reach: Over the past (almost) 8 years (we'll be celebrating our anniversary in April 2025!), we've reached 89,000 unique listeners. We currently average about 1500 listeners weekly. We've also conducted over 500 podcast interviews. Distribution: The podcast is available on all major podcast platforms, including YouTube, Amazon Music, Spotify, Apple Podcasts, and wherever else people listen to their favorite shows. Our Mission: Our podcast aims to build generational wealth through entrepreneurship. We interview entrepreneurs and innovative thinkers to share valuable insights and strategies. We appreciate you and look forward to welcoming you to the show!

Message 1 Subject: Potential Guest for The Innovative Agency: Latoya Brooks
Message 1 Content: Dear The Innovative Agency Team,
Message 2 Subject: RE: Potential Guest for The Innovative Agency: Latoya Brooks
Message 2 Content: Hi Latoya, Thank you for reaching out and for your interest in being a guest on The Innovative Agency podcast. We appreciate you taking the time to share your background with us. At this time, based on the information you provided, we don’t feel it’s the right fit for our audience. Here are the criteria we are looking for when Sharon interviews a guest on The Innovative Agency Podcast: Sharon is an attorney who helps marketing agencies protect their Intellectual Property, generate new streams of revenue from existing assets, and make sure that the 4 Critical Legal Documents are properly in place to mitigate unnecessary risks. The Innovative Agency Podcast exists to help marketing agency leaders answer the questions: “What’s Next?” How are agencies staying on the cutting edge of marketing trends? (Think AI, how agencies innovated a new process or IP to create growth, how the agency is creating new revenue streams, etc.) How are they adapting their businesses to meet new business challenges in the agency world? (Think changes in software or tools that allow for reaching customers in new ways, etc.) This is because each of these innovations also comes with legal considerations. The guest should use their expertise and stories of what they are doing from an innovation standpoint to showcase their smarts and capabilities while doing it in a way others can try to emulate. Sincerely, Lora Howdyshell Client Relationship Manager & Executive Assistant Toerek Law Office:

Message 2 Subject: Fwd: Potential Guest for Sisters with Ventures: Latoya Brooks
Message 2 Content: Hi Latoya, Apologies for the delayed response as we've gotten a bit busy on this side. Thank you for your interest in participating in the Sisters With Ventures podcast. Her podcast is typically slated for women investors or women who have experience in this area through other ventures. Below I have the crieteria for what we look for in our guests to get a better idea. What we look for in our Speakers : Accredited Investors or General Partners: You should be an accredited investor  who has invested as an angel or a general partner at a fund, with a passion for changing the status quo and a commitment to fostering diversity and inclusion within the venture capital ecosystem. Impactful Stories: We're looking for women who have overcome barriers, challenged norms, and have unique insights into the world of angel investing and venture capitalism. Commitment to Change: Our ideal speaker is someone actively working to create change, whether through educational initiatives, advocacy, or by leading by example in the investment world. Women of Color: We are committed to amplifying marginalized voices in the ecosystem. Wishing you the best in your endeavors.

Message 2 Subject: Re: Potential Guest for Max's Island: Latoya Brooks
Message 2 Content: Hey Latoya, Thanks for connecting. I’d be happy to chat with you about being a guest. Importantly, I have a strong theme and premise to my podcast and I always want guests to follow this. If this doesn’t happen, then the “magic” is never created. It’s a truly passion project for me (I have a day job and have always worked in NFP’s and human services) and is primarily driven by the transcendent experiences I get from literally every story. Each episode is generally between 25 – 35 minutes and can easily be recorded over Zoom. It’s always a casual process and only the audio track is used for the episode (no vision is used). Attached is a “Guest Information sheet” that will continue to give you some understanding of the premise … which is simply … I have found the best way to approach each episode is for the guest to focus on a single experience or story within their life, … and not necessarily their overall life story. I am a big believer in ‘pivotal’ moments and situations where you experienced something very specific as being the best places to start the episodes . I’m located in Perth, Western Australia so if you able to chat over Zoom, I’ll try to fit into your availability. Please let me know what suits. Best Regards Tony Hagan (AKA Max)

Podcast Name: Passage to Profit Show - Road to Entrepreneurship
Message 1 Subject: Potential Guest for Passage to Profit Show - Road to Entrepreneurship: Latoya Brooks
Message 1 Content: Dear Passage to Profit Show - Road to Entrepreneurship Team,
Message 2 Subject: Re: Potential Guest for Passage to Profit Show - Road to Entrepreneurship: Latoya Brooks
Message 2 Content: Hi Latoya, Thank you for your interest in Passage to Profit Show! You would be a fantastic guest on the show! Passage to Profit Show is a weekly nationally syndicated radio show & podcast showcasing entrepreneurs from various backgrounds and industries. Our show is about discussing guests' entrepreneurial journeys and their innovations. We are currently syndicated on 37 radio stations across the country on the Radio America Network and on iHeartRadio. The podcast comes out after the show airs on the radio. There are 3 options to join the show as guest: 1.) Guests can join via Zoom from their location, for which there is a $100 booking fee. 2.) We offer the additional opportunity for guests who want the full studio experience to tape their show at iHeart Studios in Manhattan! Guests will have opportunities to take photos and video in the state of the art brand new iHeart Studios and with the iHeart logo. We will also create a social media video reel that they can use for their promotions from their interview. The fee for the iHeartRadio NYC taping is $250. 3.) If you are not interested in paid opportunities but interested in the show, please still let us know. We can put you on our list and keep you in mind for a last minute spot that needs to be filled (no fee!). The show does not gain a profit from the fees, rather it helps to pay for the costs of the guest’s episode to air on 37 radio stations across the country! Attached is our media kit for review. Please let us know if you are interested in any of the 3 options.

Message 1 Content: Dear Provider's Edge | Peak Performance Guide for Healthcare Entrepreneurs Team,
Message 2 Subject: Re: Potential Guest for Provider's Edge | Peak Performance Guide for Healthcare Entrepreneurs: Latoya Brooks
Message 2 Content: Hi Latoya, First off, I want to extend a heartfelt thank you for considering the Provider's Edge show as a platform you want to be a part of. We have more than 30k downloads and ranked above top 5% globally, and syndicated across Ruko, Prime, Apple TV, and more. It's always a pleasure to hear from professionals like yourself who can add benefits to our audience. We actually produce multiple shows besides this one and have several ways to support you to amplify your messages and be happy to discuss what those packages look like. The only ways we give complimentary features on our shows are for people who are: Podcast/Radio/TV/YouTube Show Hosts: If you hosts a show in the healthcare and wellness space, we find great value in a podcast swap. This mutual exchange not only enriches content for both parties but also broadens listener bases. Strategic Partners: We're always looking to feature speakers who work with health tech companies or independent practices, indicating a shared clientele. By becoming strategic partners, we can foster a supportive environment for mutual growth. Experts and Leaders in Health Tech with a Success Story: Innovative companies who have exceed $2M in revenue and have a good product market fit can be featured on one of our shows as a founder success segment Please book a call with me here RunbeckMediaGroup.com/Coffee-Chat to discuss the above opportunities which would be a best fit for you. We are committed to maintaining a diverse and insightful array of voices on our shows, and we believe these criteria support that goal.

What I am looking for in my guests are women over 50 who are comfortable being vulnerable about how they feel about this stage in their lives, if they've faced ageism, what they really want in life now, what would help them fully align with their purpose. The show is more valuable to my listeners the more real the conversation can be! If you're 50, will be 50 this year or are over 50 and all of that sounds good to you, then I would love to meet you! Would you please share your LinkedIn profile with us?
Message 3 Subject: Re: Potential Guest for 50, NOT DEAD: Latoya Brooks
Message 3 Content: Hi Kamrin, Thanks for the additional information. I am unfortunately not over 50, so I don't think that I will be a good fit, but good to know! Best

Message 1 Subject: Potential Guest for Vegan Posse: Latoya Brooks
Message 1 Content: Dear Vegan Posse Team,
Message 2 Subject: Re: Potential Guest for Vegan Posse: Latoya Brooks
Message 2 Content: Thanks for reaching out, Latoya! I'm definitely open to having you on as a guest. Just a few questions: 1) Are you a vegan? While we at the Vegan Posse certainly recognize that people are where they are in their journeys, our current policy is that we feature only guests who are committed vegans. 2) As you may be aare, the Vegan Posse aims to give our audience a sense of our guests as PEOPLE rather than merely as "experts" or sources of information. While we are certainly happy and enthusiastic about helping get the word out about people's professional projects, are you open to sharing your story on a more personal level? 3) Can you please give a few more details about you and your vegan journey, including where you live, how long you've been evegan, and any other relevant personal details?

Message 1 Subject: Potential Guest for The F.E.E.L. Podcast - Finding Empowerment Embracing Layers: Latoya Brooks
Message 1 Content: Dear The F.E.E.L. Podcast - Finding Empowerment Embracing Layers Team,
Message 2 Subject: Re: Potential Guest for The F.E.E.L. Podcast - Finding Empowerment Embracing Layers: Latoya Brooks
Message 2 Content: Hi Latoya, Thanks so much for reaching out and being interested in being a guest on The F.E.E.L Podcast. Our framework is a little unique in how we approach our interviews, as we use a talking point format that really allows our listeners to get to know the person for who they are first, and then what they do can come up organically as we go through the conversations.  I recommend listening to a couple of episodes to get a feel for how the conversations flow. You can find those here: https://www.embracinglayers.com/episodes I am booked out through the Fall already, but would love to connect with you in November as I prepare to set up recordings for Spring 2026.  Let me know if that is something you would be interested in after you've listened to some content to hear how our conversations go. Take care, and thanks so much for the work you do on behalf of and for women! I look forward to hearing from you. Meli ssa Crook Founder & Host - The Embracing Layers Network -The F.E.E.L Podcast & Together We F.E.E.L Panel Show on YouTube Book - Embracing Layers Unapologetically: Lessons from the F.E.E.L. Podcast Collection - https://

Message 2 Content: Dear Latoya, Thank you for reaching out and for your kind words about The Criminologist podcast. Your work as a business strategist sounds impactful, and I appreciate your interest in sharing your insights with our audience. At this time, we are focused on featuring subject matter experts in Corrections and Rehabilitation, individuals with lived experience in the criminal justice system, and academics conducting research in related fields. Given our current direction, I don’t believe this would be the best fit for the podcast. That said, I truly appreciate you reaching out and wish you the best in your work.

Message 1 Subject: Potential Guest for Be BOLD Branding: Latoya Brooks
Message 1 Content: Dear Be BOLD Branding Team,
Message 2 Subject: Re: Potential Guest for Be BOLD Branding: Latoya Brooks
Message 2 Content: Hello, Latoya! My name is Cyndal and I’m with our podcast booking team! We appreciate the outreach and interest in Be BOLD Branding! Tonya and Michael personally hold small group calls for people interested in appearing, where they can learn about your story and who you serve . That helps us both in 2 ways. 1-we get to know you and where you story would best fit in the line-up and 2-sometimes candidates meet potential clients on those calls! We also belong to an ENTIRE NETWORK of top level podcasters who are looking for great guests. We can make introductions to other hosts after the call (that fit the audience you want to reach) to help you gain more visibility. OK, I say all of that to let you know that it is NOT a prerequisite to becoming a client of ours in order to be interviewed, although that happens pretty often. :) If we can be helpful to you GREAT. If not, Tonya or Michael probably know someone who can (We have a huge network of highly successful problem solvers like them). If that sounds good…here’s a little more info about us. Our 𝘉𝘦 𝘉𝘖𝘓𝘋 𝘉𝘳𝘢𝘯𝘥𝘪𝘯𝘨 podcast features coaches/consultants who have bold ‘behind the business’ stories. People we work with tend to have their hands in multiple projects (coaching, podcasting, speaking, writing, etc) but they’re not nearly as profitable as they should be. That’s why we build 𝘱𝘳𝘰𝘧𝘪𝘵𝘢𝘣𝘭𝘦 𝘱𝘦𝘳𝘴𝘰𝘯𝘢𝘭 𝘣𝘳𝘢𝘯𝘥𝘴 (it’s all we do) and most of our clients walk away charging at least 60% more for their services. For now, though…please use this link and schedule a call so Tonya can hear your story and see how it fits in the line-up! https://go.oncehub.com/VIPPodguest Cyndal Dunn- Be BOLD Branding Booking Agent Cyndal

As the host of Fintech Confidential , he engages over 1.5 million people monthly, making the show a key resource for insights in the fintech sector. Tedd is also the Founder & CEO of Voalyre , a global fintech enablement firm specializing in software and professional services. His expertise and leadership have been instrumental in driving the success of numerous startups over the past two decades, serving as an Advisory Board Member, Co-Founder, Chief Experience Officer, and Chief Strategy Officer. Tedd has provided strategic direction to both private startups and public companies such as Global Payments OpenEdge , Heartland Payment Systems , Nuvei , and TSYS . His focus on growth, innovation, and user experience has simplified the complexity of payments, leading to collaborations with major companies like Apple , Google , Amazon , Walmart , Cabela’s , and Restoration Hardware . Message 2 Content: Dear Latoya, Thank you for your interest in being a guest on STORYTELLHER. H ere’s the process: Book a 30-minute pre-call with me on Zoom using this link: https://calendly.com/deborah-kevin/precall . Once we’ve held our call, you’ll be sent an intake form to complete so we can prepare for our interview. Once that form has been successfully submitted, you’ll be sent a link to book an interview time. Our interviews are conducted on Zoom, last about 45-minutes, and are published within six weeks of recording. You’ll be provided with social media graphics and links to promote your show. I’m excited to highlight you as we elevate women’s voices, one story at a time! With gratitude and excitement, Debby Deborah Kevin Author, Editor, and Speaker www.deborahkevin.com | debby

Message 1 Subject: Re: Potential Guest for Growing In Community: Latoya Brooks
Message 1 Content: Hi Latoya, Thank you for reaching out and for your kind words about Growing In Community! We’re honored that you admire the work we’re doing, and we’re absolutely excited to hear about your experience as a business strategist. The topics you mentioned—transforming challenges into opportunities, navigating change, building confidence, and turning setbacks into stepping stones—are incredibly relevant, and we believe our listeners would greatly benefit from your insights. Your 15 years of experience are impressive, and we’d love to explore the possibility of having you as a guest on our show. That said, we’d love to get to know you a bit more beyond your professional expertise. Would you mind sharing more about your personal journey, your passions, and how you connect with your audience outside of your work? Additionally, if you have any social media handles or personal platforms where we can learn more about your story, that would be fantastic! Season two of Growing In Community will be resuming in June, and we’re currently planning the lineup of guests. Let’s schedule a time to discuss the details and how we can best highlight your expertise and personal story. Please let me know your availability, and we can arrange a call or meeting to move forward. Looking forward to connecting soon!

Message 1 Subject: RE: Potential Guest for Yachting Channel: Latoya Brooks
Message 1 Content: Hello Latoya and Karine, Latoya, thank you for reaching out to Yachting International Radio. I’d like to introduce you to Karine Rayson, host of Forward Watch , a powerful and insightful series focused on leadership within the yachting industry. Karine is the owner of The Crew Coach and an expert in leadership development, mental well-being, and professional growth for captains, crew, and industry professionals. Karine, Latoya recently expressed interest in being featured on our platform, and I believe Forward Watch could be a great fit for her expertise. Latoya, Karine’s show explores the evolving landscape of leadership at sea, fostering meaningful discussions that provide valuable guidance to those navigating careers in the yachting world. I’ll let you both take it from here to explore potential opportunities. Looking forward to seeing where this conversation leads! Kindest
